title.narrative: HEALTH, CHILD SURVIVAL, NUTRITION & Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH)

description.narrative: 3.5: Strengthened capacity to ensure the rights of the child to survival, growth and development with equity in all contexts, including humanitarian, recovery and fragile situations, which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 3. UNICEF supported programmes are responsive to development challenges, in line with corporate and regional priorities, strategies, principles and guidelines
